<doc id="69290" wikidata="Q7452651" url="?curid=69290" title="Seraiah">
<text>Seraiah or Sraya (שְׂרָיָה &quot;Soldier/Prince/Princess of/is the LORD&quot;, Standard Hebrew &quot;Səraya&quot;, Tiberian Hebrew &quot;Śərāyā&quot;) is the name of several people mentioned in the Hebrew Bible, and a name with other non-biblical uses.

==Biblical characters==

* Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth

* Seraiah ben Neriah

==Others==
*Sariah - according to the Book of Mormon, the wife of Lehi, and the mother of Laman, Lemuel, Sam, and Nephi
*Zrahia, a religious moshav in southern Israel.

==Contemporary==
*Serayah McNeill (born 1995), American actress, singer

